-3476(83)80528-9">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/6822928/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Anterior+sacral+defects%3A+an+autosomal+dominantly+inherited+condition&amp;author=VD+Yates&amp;author=RS+Wilroy&amp;author=GL+Whitington&amp;author=JC+Simmons&amp;publication_year=1983&amp;journal=J+Pediatr&amp;pages=239-242&amp;doi=10.1016%2FS0022-3476%2883%2980528-9&amp;pmid=6822928">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">45.</div><div id="r45" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Emans PJ, van Aalst J, van Heurn EL, et al. The Currarino triad: neurosurgical considerations. <em>Neurosurgery</em> 2006;58(5):924–929.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1227/01.NEU.0000209945.87233.6A">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16639328/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=The+Currarino+triad%3A+neurosurgical+considerations&amp;author=PJ+Emans&amp;author=J+van+Aalst&amp;author=EL+van+Heurn&amp;publication_year=2006&amp;journal=Neurosurgery&amp;pages=924-929&amp;doi=10.1227%2F01.NEU.0000209945.87233.6A&amp;pmid=16639328">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">46.</div><div id="r46" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Low G, Irwin GJ, Haddock G, Maroo SV. Currarino triad: characteristic appearances on magnetic resonance imaging and plain radiography. <em>Australas Radiol</em> 2006;50(3):249–251.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1440-1673.2006.01572.x">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a 